job.title: IMMT Secretariat Assistant Recruitment  2021 – Apply online for 14  Posts in Odisha
job.body:
Total vacancies:14

Name of the Posts:

  • Junior Secretariat Assistant & Jr. Stenographer

Description

New Central Government Jobs have been published by the Institute of Minerals & Materials Technology for the posts of Junior Secretariat Assistant. If you are finding a government job in Odisha then it is an opportunity for you. You can fill the online application for these posts in Odisha, from 20.05.2021, and till 21.06.2021. If you are interested in all these posts in Odisha and if eligible, please check out the details given below, which have been given age limit, educational qualification pay scale, etc.


Application fee:

  • The mode of application is Online
  • No information about the application fee

Educational qualification:

  • To apply for a Junior Secretariat Assistant posts Odisha, your 12th class must be completed by a recognized Board.

Important dates:

  •  The starting date to apply in these posts is the 20.05.2021
  •  The last date to apply in these posts is 21.06.2021

Age Limit Criteria:

  • For General Candidate, you should be between 21 to 40 years old. 

IMMT Junior Secretariat Assistant Pay Scale:

  • According to the information given by the Central Government and as per the 7th pay commission, the teacher's monthly salary is ₹19900 – Rs. 63200/-

How to apply for IMMT Secretariat Assistant Recruitment 2021?

Press the Apply Now button above. You can directly and easily start the application process for these posts in Odisha. Fill in your details and submit it

  • Or follow all the steps given below,
  •  First, go to the official website of IMMT and register yourself on the portal.
  • Find the notification, log in and then provide the details and documents asked BY IMMT.
  • Then save it and complete the application submission.
  • Then to fully complete the process you have to submit the application fee.
  • And finally, download the application form for future purposes.
